lyrics:
I've been hearing symphonies
Before, all I heard was silence
A rhapsody for you and me
And every melody is timeless
Life was stringing me along
Then you came and you cut me loose
Was solo, singing on my own
Now I can't find the key without you

And now your song is on repeat
And I'm dancin' on to your heartbeat
And when you're gone, I feel incomplete
So, if you want the truth

I just wanna be part of your symphony
Will you hold me tight and not let go?

imageDescription: A simple and creative image that best represents the song "Symphony" is a pair of intertwined musical notes, one representing the male vocalist and the other representing the female vocalist. The notes are vibrant and colorful, symbolizing the harmony and connection between the two voices. In the background, there is a radio broadcasting waves of love, representing the power and impact of their song.
